        "📌 ComfyUI Workflow Notes\n**Author:** Sharvin Suntoobacus  \n**YouTube Channel:** CodeCraftersCorner  \n**Patreon:** [Support on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/CodeCraftersCorner)\n\n---\n\n### ℹ️ About This Workflow\nThis workflow provides a streamlined method for generating iterative image-to-image variations. It is specifically designed to help users—even those with limited drawing skills—refine initial sketches into high-quality artwork through an automated looping logic. By leveraging **Qwen-VL** for image analysis and adjustable **denoising strength**, users can achieve precise control over how much the output deviates from the original input.\n\n### 🎥 Tutorial / Guide\n[Watch on YouTube](https://youtu.be/BZ1v99UiEd0)  \n\n### 📥 Model Selection\nThis workflow is versatile and does not require a specific model setup.\n*   **Default Setup:** Uses the **Flux.1 Dev** template.\n*   **Compatibility:** You can use any model from your `templates` folder, including **SDXL**, **Z-Image Turbo**, or **Flux.2**.\n*   **Configuration:** Simply select your preferred model via the **Load Diffusion Model** node. No manual file placement is required if you are using existing ComfyUI templates.\n\n### 💡 Notes\n*   **Denoising Strength:** This is the key variable for variation. Values between **0.4 and 0.9** are recommended for the best balance between creativity and consistency.\n*   **The Loop Logic:** The \"Load Image from Output\" node allows you to feed your last generation back into the input, enabling iterative design improvements.\n*   **Prompting:** The prompt is split into \"Style\" and \"Scene\" sections to allow for better granular control over the final look.\n\n**Credit:** Please credit Sharvin Suntoobacus and share the YouTube Channel **Code Crafters Corner** when sharing this workflow.  \n**Support:** Your support on Patreon helps me continue creating these guides!  \n[YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/@CodeCraftersCorner) | [Patreon Page](https://www.patreon.com/CodeCraftersCorner)\n\n🙏 **Thank you for your support!**"
